---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Privacy Policy | retaliatoryfirecalc.com';
const description = 'Privacy policy for retaliatoryfirecalc.com — what data we collect, the case-review form, how it is used, and your choices regarding cookies and advertising.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> July 2026</p>

  <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>Browsing the calculator, guides, and reference pages on retaliatoryfirecalc.com collects nothing personally identifying. We do not require account registration, do not store calculator inputs, and do not transmit the information you enter into our calculator to any server — all calculations run locally in your browser.</p>
  <p>If you choose to submit the Workplace Retaliation case-review form on our homepage, we collect what you enter: your name, phone number, email address, a description of your case, and the time you gave consent. That form is optional and separate from the calculator itself.</p>
  <p>We use Google AdSense to serve advertising and Google Analytics to understand aggregate traffic patterns. Both services collect usage data as described in Google&rsquo;s privacy policy. Google AdSense may use cookies and device identifiers to serve ads relevant to your interests based on your browsing activity across sites that participate in Google&rsquo;s advertising network.</p>

  <h2>The Case-Review Form and Attorney Sharing</h2>
  <p>If you submit the case-review form, your name, phone number, email address, and case details are shared with one or more attorneys or their agents licensed to practice in your jurisdiction, so they can evaluate your situation and contact you about it. The Click Lab Agency LLC, which operates retaliatoryfirecalc.com, is not a law firm, does not provide legal advice, and does not vet, endorse, or guarantee the attorneys in this network. Submitting the form does not create an attorney-client relationship with The Click Lab Agency LLC or with any attorney until and unless that attorney separately agrees to represent you. The Click Lab Agency LLC may be compensated for these referrals.</p>
  <p>By submitting the form, you separately consent to be contacted by phone, text, and email &mdash; including by automated dialing technology &mdash; by The Click Lab Agency LLC and the attorneys or agents your information is shared with. That consent is not required to use any other part of this site, and you can decline it simply by not submitting the form.</p>

  <h2>Cookies</h2>
  <p>Our site uses cookies placed by Google AdSense for advertising purposes and Google Analytics for aggregate traffic measurement. We do not place first-party cookies for tracking or advertising. You can opt out of personalized Google advertising by visiting <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ad Settings</a>. You can also manage cookie preferences in your browser settings.</p>

  <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>The third-party services operating on this site are:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Google AdSense</strong> — display advertising. Subject to <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google&rsquo;s Privacy Policy</a>.</li>
    <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> — aggregate traffic analysis (page views, session counts, general geographic distribution). We do not use Google Analytics to identify individual visitors. Subject to Google&rsquo;s Privacy Policy.</li>
    <li><strong>Attorneys or their agents</strong> — if you submit the case-review form, as described above.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Data Retention</h2>
  <p>We do not store visitor browsing data on our own servers. Case-review form submissions are retained and shared with attorneys as described above. Google Analytics data is retained per Google&rsquo;s standard retention settings. You can request deletion of your Google Analytics data by using Google&rsquo;s opt-out tools.</p>

  <h2>Your Choices and Opting Out</h2>
  <p>The simplest opt-out is not to submit the case-review form. If you've already submitted it and want your information removed or want to withdraw consent to be contacted, email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> with the subject line <strong>[OPT-OUT]</strong>, or visit <a href="https://theclicklab.agency/optout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">theclicklab.agency/optout</a>.</p>

  <h2>California Privacy Rights (CCPA/CPRA)</h2>
  <p>California residents have the right to know what personal information is collected, the right to delete personal information, and the right to opt out of the sale or sharing of personal information. Sharing your case-review submission with attorneys in exchange for compensation may be considered a &ldquo;sale&rdquo; or &ldquo;sharing&rdquo; of personal information under the CCPA/CPRA, and you can opt out through either channel above. Anonymous browsing of the calculator and guides alone is never sold or shared, because we don't collect anything from it. For questions about your California privacy rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>.</p>

  <h2>European Privacy Rights (GDPR)</h2>
  <p>If you are located in the EEA, UK, or Switzerland and choose to submit the case-review form, the legal basis for processing your information is your consent, which you may withdraw at any time using the opt-out channels above. Browsing the site itself does not involve processing personal data about you.</p>

  <h2>Children&rsquo;s Privacy</h2>
  <p>This site is not directed to children under 13 and we do not knowingly collect information from children.</p>

  <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this privacy policy to reflect changes in our practices or applicable law. The date at the top of this page will be updated when changes are made.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions about this privacy policy? Email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>.</p>
</BaseLayout>
